<item>
            <title>[LU-12170] sanity 43a may fail as it&apos;s not a binary</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12170</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description></description>
                <environment>locally I&amp;#39;m getting lots of sanity/43a failures with the following output:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;sanity test_43a: @@@@@@ FAIL: expected error, got success &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
basically it means that multiop binary started from Lustre can be open for write which is not correct. &lt;br/&gt;
according to the logs multiop file is open for execution and closed right away while it&amp;#39;s supposed to stay open util SIGKILL is sent. not sure about exact sequence, but it looks related to libtool wrapping. &lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
